  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Alpha Phase Child Growth Monitor</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving the Algorithm of the Child Growth Monitor. Creating the Coordination structures for free lancers and coordination in India and linking the technology better with the technology development team in Germany. Financing for HoP and technical Expert staffing costs of technology development in Germany for Alpha phase.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Today: Our target group are children 0.5-5 years of age in 51 countries suffering from severe hunger. Our primary user group are professional healthcare workers taking anthropometric measurements of children. In the future: In the future we aim at opening up our target and user group: Child Growth Monitor to be used in more than 51 countries; to be used also by parents, teachers, pharmacists, etc.; to be used for overweight children; possibly to be used for children older than 5 years.</narrative>
  </description>
